jobs_results.description:
Our client is looking for a visionary Data Science Lead (Tech) to develop scientific and analytical solutions to identify drivers of technology revolution.

Mandatory Skill-set
• Bachelor's Degree or Master's Degree in Statistics, Decision Science, Computer Science, Economics or other relevant majors;
• Has around 5 years of experience in technology consulting, strategy or research;
• Deep understanding in new technologies such as Artificial Intelligence, Data Science, 5G, IOT;
• Good knowledge of scenario planning and long term forecasting principles and practices;
• Good knowledge on data mining tools and techniques (diagnostic and predictive) and data warehousing;
• Proficient in statistical and data visualisation tools such as SAS, Qilk Sense Tableau, R and Python;
• Good knowledge of the tech ecosystem;
• Possesses excellent communication skills to engage with leading experts and senior management;
• Strong problem solving and critical thinking skills, and able to work to derive... economic values from strategic explorations;
Desired Skill-set
• Good understanding of Machine Learning and Deep Learning concepts.

Responsibilities
• Deliver deep insights with the appropriate analytics methodologies and techniques to help departments have a better understanding of technological and socioeconomic trends, geopolitical landscapes, and drivers/dynamics of change;
• Conduct analysis and build analytic models for technology foresight, optimise decisions and inject predictive intelligence to business decisions;
• Able to interpret technical statistical results and communicate insights through storytelling;
• Sharing of strategic foresight, viewpoints and perspectives on strategic moves and economic values to management;
• Maintain and enhance data-driven technology intelligence platform to ensure continuing relevance to business users.
Should you be interested in this career opportunity, please send in your updated resume to apply@sciente.com at the earliest.

When you apply, you voluntarily consent to the disclosure, collection and use of your personal data for employment/recruitment and related purposes in accordance with the SCIENTE Group Privacy Policy, a copy of which is published at SCIENTEs website (https://www.sciente.com/privacy-policy).

Confidentiality is assured, and only shortlisted candidates will be notified for interviews.

